FBIS4-65737 "drweu099_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-099 Daily Report 23 May 1994 SPAIN Army Officer Dies in Madrid Car Explosion Army Officer Dies in Madrid Car Explosion LD2305075394 Madrid Teletexto TVE in Spanish 0737 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305075394 Madrid Teletexto TVE Spanish BFN [Text] A lieutenant in the Army Engineering Corps, who was 59, died when his car exploded on the N-V road (Madrid-Extremadura). The explosion practically destroyed the car in which Miguel Peralta Utrera, the officer, was driving. The car had Madrid license plates. Officers from the municipal police, firefighters, and Red Cross ambulances have gone to the scene of the attack. The road has been closed to traffic.
